50|$|As <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts</b> {{dismantle}} <b>the</b> cartel {{piece by}} piece, they eventually {{are given the}} option to go after El Sueño. Upon raiding an empty Cartel stronghold, <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts</b> receive a call from El Sueño. He attempts to bribe <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts</b> into working for the Santa Blanca, promising huge benefits. <b>The</b> <b>Ghosts</b> refuse. Ordered to regroup with Bowman, <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts</b> find her captive {{in the presence of}} the rebels. Told that Katari has betrayed them, <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts</b> race to El Sueño's mausoleum to capture him. After fighting their way through the enemy opposition, <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts</b> and Bowman find and surround El Sueño, who has just beheaded Katari. Despite El Sueño surrendering to <b>the</b> <b>Ghosts,</b> Bowman receives a call from her superiors, informing that Sueño had made a deal with the Department of Justice to give up the heads of other cartels in exchange for immunity.|$|R
